</div></section></section><section id="sec3"><h3 class="pmc_sec_title">DNA sequence determination.</h3>
<p>The 16S rRNA, <em>lipL32</em>, <em>lipL41</em>, and <em>ompL1</em> gene sequences were obtained by direct sequencing of PCR amplicons generated with <em>Tth</em> polymerase (Clonetech, Palo Alto, Calif.). Some of the genes analyzed have been previously reported (<a href="#r13" class="usa-link" aria-describedby="r13">13</a>, <a href="#r14" class="usa-link" aria-describedby="r14">14</a>, <a href="#r19" class="usa-link" aria-describedby="r19">19</a>, <a href="#r38" class="usa-link" aria-describedby="r38">38</a>, <a href="#r40" class="usa-link" aria-describedby="r40">40</a>). Previously unpublished sequences have been submitted to GenBank (see below). Primers used for sequencing are listed in Table <a href="#t2" class="usa-link">2</a>.</p>
